Package: ucminfcpp
Title: Unconstrained Nonlinear Optimization via C and Rcpp
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hans Bruun", "Nielsen", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original Fortran algorithm"),
    person("Stig Bousgaard", "Mortensen", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original R/Fortran/C implementation"),
    person("ucminfcpp", "Maintainer", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maintainer@example.com")
  )
Description: A migration of the UCMINF unconstrained nonlinear optimization
    algorithm from Fortran+C+R to pure C and Rcpp. Phase 1 translates the
    Fortran core to C; Phase 2 wraps it with an Rcpp interface. The algorithm
    is of quasi-Newton type with BFGS updating of the inverse Hessian and a
    soft line search with trust-region radius monitoring.
